<br>
It is just like a regular atk increase.  It will shift your distribution of hits.  And this of course increases your average hit and makes you hit for max more often. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gryzx@thesteelwarrior>Gryzx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/15/03 10:41 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   not quite the same as atk.</span><hr size=1> It's not quite the same as atk, since atk isn't supposed to increase your max hit.  Str on the other hand can increase your max hit, you seem to get a bonus attached to you hits if you have high str.  <br>
<br>
This is easiest to see on a low lvl character that you know is supposed to be capped.  If you make an ogre and max out his strength while his hits are supposed to be capped the strength will increase your max beyond the cap.  The best I can tell is high strength adds some amount of damage to each hit, kindof like the damage bonus does. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thelionfist>The Lionfist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/15/03 10:44 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: not quite the same as atk.</span><hr size=1> Like AC is a shown mixture of the &quot;real&quot; mitigation and avoidance AC, I am pretty sure ATK as we see it is a shown mixture of the &quot;real&quot;, to-hit and damage ATK's.<br>
<br>
The STR increases the amount of damage you hit for by shifting your max hits up, but doesnt effect your chance to hit.<br>
<br>
The question is, does STR shift all hits up some, or only the ceiling? <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~carriedingus/lionfist.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=darklightsoulweaver>Darklight Soulweaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/15/03 10:57 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: not quite the same as atk.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>It's not quite the same as atk, since atk isn't supposed to increase your max hit<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
