If the 52 warrior hit 404,  it's a critical hit.  Check your log.  It would be impossible for it not to be a critical -- level 52 is 4 damage tables behind me.  ATK (whether it be raw atk or atk generated from higher strength) shifts your modal hit higher on the damage table.  The higher your ATK the more you'll see hits for max damage.  ATK has zero affect on hit %.  Hit % is a mainly function of your level vs. the mobs level.  I believe it may factor in a little bit of weapon skill as well tho weapon skill also directly affects your ATK. <p>[<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=59000" target="top">Overlord</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->] Marshall Kiras D`Maxar (Dark Elf) zone: nexus</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kirasdm>KirasDM</A> at: 4/15/03 12:50:15 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=darklightsoulweaver>Darklight Soulweaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/15/03 12:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: not quite the same as atk.</span><hr size=1> <br>
