<br>
Maybe for a level 50s character that doesn't yet have his weapon skills maxed at 250 and offense at 252, the atk increase can raise the max damage, but once your skills cap, you get a minor increase each level and that's it.<br>
<br>
Yes, Labiara, stats have an effect &gt; 0.  Also, I am glad to hear that dex has some real positive benefits for archery.  IIRC, those shaman tests showed around a 3 percent increase in procs for a 100pt increase in dex.  The point is, you get vastly superior bang for the buck investing in gear that pumps your hp and ac.  There comes a point in the game post ST when all your melee stats are capped 99 percent of the time anyway.  This has changed somewhat with the raised caps, but capped stats are still quite easy to acheive once you start down the path of a raiding guild.  So, focus your attention on hp and ac, the stats will follow.<br>
<br>
