</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zukobim>Zukobim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 77<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/15/03 11:00 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: not quite the same as atk.</span><hr size=1> Max hits can be calculated with the following formulas (atleast they work up to level 60. They are derived from data before PoP, so level 61-65 is not tested.).<br>
<br>
Max damage = ((Str + Skill + Level)/100)* damage + mainhand bonus <br>
<br>
Damage bonus for 1H weapon (only affect mainhand weapon) = (level-25)/3 rounded down <br>
<br>
Damage bonus for 2H weapon = look at the weapons info ingame<br>
<br>
STR directly affects the max damage and it also affects ATK.<br>
<br>
ATK determines how much you hit for inside the hit-range (miss-&gt;max damage)<br>
Items that adds raw ATK will make your average hits increase, but not your max hits.<br>
<br>
