<br>
I don't try to max them all, it just happens when you start using raid level gear.<br>
<br>
The goal is hp/ac/raw atk/resists/regen.  The other stats just come with the package.  I would wear gear that put me at 6000hp 1400ac 1400atk and 6regen/tick with all melee stats at 120 way before I would wear gear that put me at 5400hp 1200ac 1300atk and 255 in all melee stats.  That may be a little lopsided, but the point remains, until proven otherwise, the best evidence I have seen shows stats have much less relative value than hp/ac/atk.  Coupling that fact with the reality that <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>you will max your stats whether you want to or not just by getting raid level gear</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->; it is easy to see that choosing gear based on stats instead of based on ac/hp/atk is a suboptimal course of action and also irrelevant because of the inevitablility of maxxing your stats.<br>
<br>
That said, this thread has aroused my curiosity, and now, with my taxes filed, I would like to put some testing into seeing the exact effects. <p><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5309"target="_blank"><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR = 10,10,900><b>Korak Sarathai - Barbarian Warlord</b></FONT><BR></a><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=12530"target="_blank"><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR = 900,10,10><b>Dumesh Uhl'Belk - Retired Troll Reaver</b></FONT><BR></a>Those who will not reason are bigots; those who cannot are fools; and those who dare not are slaves. -- Lord Byron
