<br>
The raw ATK is what gives you the DPS increase, not the stats.  There were days when I was in my mid 50's that I could run around with 255 in all melee stats due to buff stacking issues that were in place when Harnessing of Spirit was implemented...it was zero issue to give anyone something on the order of 140 str and 110 dex, which maxed virtually anyone.  Did I see a DPS increase?  Ya, pretty minor tho.  All it really did was let me see the higher hits that were possible from my weapons, it wasn't anything earth shattering.  But as long as I had mana on the shaman, and I wasn't doing much with her anyway, why not?<br>
<br>
Now fast forward to level 60 when I scribed avatar.  Holy @#%$ dude...the difference is complete nite and day.   100atk provides easily 10 fold the benefit of some strength and dex.  You don't just have the capability to hit harder, your entire damage spectrum shifts to the right.  Minimum hits are almost completely non existant, and it's very likely you'll see 3-4 of whatever the max hit is on your weapon in your chat box at one time.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Most of the time a question like this comes up, people reference the same OLD OLD tests.<br>
But 3 years ... and HOW MANY PATCHES AGO?<br>
I think some new tests might be in order. Cause people are always asking for stat buffs from shamen.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Ya well, some people still wear jagged bands and black pearl jewelry.  Some people insist that charisma provides a benefi for charm.  That doesn't make it correct...that makes it an undying rumor.  Not everyone playing EQ reads message boards where people discuss the current state of affairs with various systems in the game.  Some people are still using what the game manual tells them, and some people are still using whatever logic they used in games like AD&amp;D regarding stats and assuming it will be the same in EQ.  It's not.  Stats DO play a role.  However, they play such a miniscule role that it's not an effective course of action to focus on them over stats that have a difference you can see...such as AC/HP/ATK. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=48986">Marshall Haass Wolvesbane</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=71943">Venerable Cagna Soulshaker</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <br>
